abstract: |
  DTQEM v44.0 (Decoherence from Time‑scale Quantum Effective Mismatch) introduces a unified framework for quantum decoherence based on proper‑time discrepancy between the particle and the measuring device.

  The core equation (D0 – baseline model) is:

      V_eff = V_source(d) × exp(-γ_φ·τ) × exp(-|Δτ|/τ_c)

  where:
  - V_source(d) = |sinc(π·src_size·d/(λ·L_src))| (Van Cittert-Zernike)
  - exp(-γ_φ·τ) (Lindblad environmental decoherence)
  - exp(-|Δτ|/τ_c) (DTQEM proper-time decoherence hypothesis)
  - Δτ = τ × (1 - 1/γ), τ = a/v, γ = 1/√(1-β²)
  - τ_c – the only free parameter

  The framework includes five interactive code modules:

  1. dtqem_double_slit_forward_v44.py – Double-slit interference (forward model)
  2. dtqem_double_slit_inverse_v44.py – Double-slit parameter extraction (inverse model)
  3. dtqem_qubit_decoherence_v44.py – Qubit decoherence simulator with Bloch sphere
  4. dtqem_zeeman_effect_v44.py – Zeeman effect simulator with energy levels
  5. dtqem_wave_code_v44.py – Core wave functions and propagation

  All modules feature:
  - ipywidgets interactive sliders (zero overlap with plots)
  - Dark theme professional interface
  - Real-time parameter updates
  - Export to PNG
  - Reset to defaults
  - Google Colab / Jupyter compatibility

  This version adopts the D0 baseline (simple exponential decoherence) without additional complexity (no β, no τ_c(γ), no τ_sat). Future extensions are explicitly deferred to later versions.

